==Administrative career==

===Partizan vice-president (2000&ndash;2004)===
In fall 2000, shortly after retiring from playing professionally, Danilovi<U+0107> became co-vice president of his old club [[KK Partizan]], working under new club president [[Vlade Divac]]. The appointment came about on initiative by club official [[Ivica Da<U+010D>i<U+0107>]] during the time of political upheaval in Serbia in the wake of the [[overthrow of Slobodan Milo<U+0161>evi<U+0107>|Slobodan Milo<U+0161>evi<U+0107> overthrow]]. Da<U+010D>i<U+0107>, the club's outgoing president and, more importantly, a suddenly marginalized politician who, due to his association with Milo<U+0161>evi<U+0107>, was forced to leave his post at the club, saw that various state-owned companies and community property were being taken over in a dubious manner during the power vacuum that resulted from r<U+00E9>gime change, Da<U+010D>i<U+0107> saw it prudent to bring the club's two former greats as a safeguard against the same happening to KK Partizan.<ref>{{Citation|title=Divac savetuje Da<U+010D>i<U+0107>a |url=http://www.blic.rs/Vesti/Politika/61059/Divac-savetuje-Dacica| date=2008-10-16| publisher=Blic}}</ref>

Since Divac was at the time still an active player in the NBA with [[Sacramento Kings]], Danilovi<U+0107> essentially ran KK Partizan.

Inheriting a head coach Darko Russo, Danilovi<U+0107> let him finish out the season before hiring old mentor and friend [[Du<U+0161>ko Vujo<U+0161>evi<U+0107>]] during summer 2001. Vujo<U+0161>evi<U+0107> immediately started producing results, winning the league title in 2001-02, endind the three-year winning run of [[KK Budu<U+0107>nost]]. It was the first of nine consecutive league trophies under his command. Though continually cash-strapped, under the command of Danilovi<U+0107>, Divac, and sporting director Dragan Todori<U+0107>, the club instituted a model of bringing up domestic young players from its own youth setup or smaller clubs in [[Serbia and Montenegro]] rather than relying on foreign imports. It proved a winner both on the court and business-wise as Partizan sold its best player in regular intervals (usually every summer) and then re-invested that money into the youth system or acquiring talented youngsters from smaller clubs while making sure that squad can function with other players stepping up. Under this model, in summer 2003 [[Milo<U+0161> Vujani<U+0107>]] was sold to [[Fortitudo Bologna]] while the following summer 2004 [[Nenad Krsti<U+0107>]] got sold to [[New Jersey Nets]]. The club managed to win the domestic league FR Yugoslavia/Serbia-Montenegro league year after year, ensuring a [[Euroleague]] spot, which was essential for its bottom line.

Simultaneously, Danilovi<U+0107> was very much against his club joining the regional [[Adriatic League]]. However, by 2004, Partizan was essentially forced into the regional competition because its Euroleague spot now depended on competing regionally rather than domestically. This also brought about change in the club's business model as in the summer of 2004 they brought in already established national team players 27-year-old [[Dejan Milojevi<U+0107>]] from [[KK Budu<U+0107>nost]] and 29-year-old [[Milan Gurovi<U+0107>]] from [[KK Vojvodina]] to bolster the squad ahead of the start of [[2004<U+2013>05 ABA Goodyear League|competition]] in Adriatic League. It would prove to be one of Danilovi<U+0107>'s last orders of business at the club as he soon left KK Partizan.

===Partizan president (2007&ndash;present)===
In 2007 Danilovi<U+0107> returned to KK Partizan, this time as president. That year, he was placed on probation by the Serbian Basketball Federation due to a physical altercation with referee Marko Juras after a playoff game versus [[KK Hemofarm]] in [[Vr<U+0161>ac]]. Danilovi<U+0107> was originally suspended from all basketball-related activity for two years, but the federation later decided to reduce the punishment.<ref>[http://www.b92.net/sport/vesti.php?yyyy=2007&mm=09&dd=18&nav_id=264040 Danilovi<U+0107>u smanjena kazna za Vr<U+0161>ac]</ref>

== Personal life ==
Danilovi<U+0107> is married to Svetlana Danilovi<U+0107>, an [[Radio Television of Serbia|RTS]] sports reporter. The couple have three children.

He was also involved with [[Group Seven Children's Foundation|Group Seven]], a charity organization founded by seven Serbian basketball players.

On 11 February 2009, Danilovi<U+0107> filed a lawsuit against Worldwide Associates<ref>[http://dockets.justia.com/docket/indiana/insdce/1:2009cv00151/22154/ DANILOVIC v. WORLDWIDE ASSOCIATES, LLC et al]</ref> (a limited-liability company based in [[Carmel, Indiana]] and represented by Rick Suder and George Grkinich) alleging investment fraud connected to $4 million he gave the company to manage.<ref>[http://www.ibj.com/former-pro-basketball-players-accuse-firm-of-investment-fraud/PARAMS/article/19376 Former basketball players accuse firm of investment fraud];''[[Indianapolis Business Journal]]'', 16 April 2010</ref> Previously, Grkinich was also involved with Group Seven.<ref>[http://newspaperarchive.com/daily-herald/2005-07-16/page-155?tag=george+grkinich&rtserp=people/g/grjigian-grobleck/grkinich/george-grkinich NBA Stars Play a Round for the Kids];''[[Daily Herald (Arlington Heights)|Daily Herald]]'', 16 July 2005</ref>

===May 2013 stabbing===
In the early morning hours of Saturday, 18 May 2013, 43-year-old Danilovi<U+0107> was stabbed during a bar brawl in Belgrade, sustaining injuries to his head, arms, and abdomen, for which he received surgery at Belgrade's Urgentni centar.<ref>[http://www.nytimes.com/2013/05/19/sports/basketball/predrag-danilovic-stabbed-in-brawl.html?_r=0 Former N.B.A. Player Stabbed in Brawl];''The New York Times'', 18 May 2013</ref>

From the press reports, Danilovi<U+0107> had been drinking and eating at the Kafanica bar, a [[kafana]]-type establishment in the [[Ko<U+0161>utnjak]] neighbourhood, together with a party of friends,<ref>[http://www.blic.rs/naslovna-stampano-izdanje/732/izdanje-za-20-05-2013 Prijatelji su, ali i nezgodni kad popiju];''Blic'', 20 May 2013</ref> including the bar's owner, Danilovi<U+0107>'s close friend, Branko "Fido" Filipovi<U+0107>,<ref>[http://www.blic.rs/naslovna-stampano-izdanje/733/izdanje-za-21-05-2013 Od grljenja do noza u stomak za pet minuta];''Blic'', 21 May 2013</ref> before a fight broke out around 2:20am between Filipovi<U+0107> and Danilovi<U+0107>. Filipovi<U+0107> reportedly struck Danilovi<U+0107> in the head with an ashtray<ref>[http://www.mondo.rs/s290469/Info/Info/Hronika_i_Drustvo/Danilovic_izboden_u_svadji_medju_prijateljima.html Danilovi<U+0107> izboden "u sva<U+0111>i me<U+0111>u prijateljima"];MTS Mondo, 18 May 2013</ref> prompting someone from the bar to call an ambulance, which Danilovi<U+0107> refused upon their arrival, sending them away.<ref>[http://www.b92.net/info/vesti/index.php?yyyy=2013&mm=05&dd=18&nav_category=16&nav_id=714914 Predrag Danilovi<U+0107> izboden no<U+017E>em];B92, 18 May 2013</ref> The fight between the two continued with Filipovi<U+0107> now stabbing Danilovi<U+0107> in the abdomen, and injured Danilovi<U+0107> driving by himself to the hospital.<ref>[http://www.novosti.rs/vesti/naslovna/hronika/aktuelno.291.html:434418-Predrag-Danilovic-ranjen-u-kafanskoj-svadji Predrag Danilovi<U+0107> ranjen u kafanskoj sva<U+0111>i];''Vecernje novosti'', 18 May 2013</ref> Due to the nature of his injuries, considered "life-threatening",<ref>[http://www.b92.net/info/vesti/index.php?yyyy=2013&mm=05&dd=18&nav_category=16&nav_id=714982 MUP:Istra<U+017E>ujemo napad na Danilovi<U+0107>a];B92, 18 May 2013</ref> Danilovic underwent emergency surgery and afterwards got placed in intensive care in stable condition.<ref>[http://sport.blic.rs/Kosarka/Domaca-kosarka-i-ABA/233330/KK-Partizan-Predsednik-Danilovic-je-operisan-u-stabilnom-je-stanju-zelimo-mu-brz-oporavak KK Partizan: Predsednik Danilovi<U+0107> je operisan, u stabilnom je stanju, <U+017E>elimo mu brz oporavak];''Blic'', 18 May 2013</ref> During the day Danilovi<U+0107> was visited at the hospital by the Serbian prime minister [[Ivica Da<U+010D>i<U+0107>]] (incidentally Danilovi<U+0107>'s personal friend and predecessor at the post of KK Partizan president), Serbian deputy prime minister [[Aleksandar Vu<U+010D>i<U+0107>]] and sports minister [[Alisa Mari<U+0107>]]. Talking to the press, prime minister Da<U+010D>i<U+0107> described the circumstances of Danilovic's stabbing as the "traditional Serbian quarrel between friends".<ref>[http://www.blic.rs/Vesti/Hronika/383188/Dacic-Danilovic-je-povredjen-u-tradicionalnoj-srpskoj-svadji-medju-prijateljima Da<U+010D>i<U+0107>: Danilovi<U+0107> je povre<U+0111>en u tradicionalnoj srpskoj sva<U+0111>i me<U+0111>u prijateljima];''Blic'', 18 May 2013</ref>

On 20 May, Serbian police issued an arrest warrant for Branko Filipovi<U+0107> after unsuccessfully trying to summon him for questioning.<ref>[http://www.b92.net/info/vesti/index.php?yyyy=2013&mm=05&dd=20&nav_category=206&nav_id=715528 Poternica za prijateljem Danilovi<U+0107>a];B92, 20 May 2013</ref> Danilovi<U+0107> got out of the hospital on 26 May<ref>[http://www.blic.rs/Vesti/Hronika/384633/Predrag-Danilovic-izasao-iz-bolnice-a-Fidi-jos-uvek-u-bekstvu Predrag Danilovi<U+0107> iza<U+0161>ao iz bolnice, a Fidi jo<U+0161> uvek u bekstvu];''Blic'', 26 May 2013</ref> and was seen in public at the [[Belgrade Airport]] awaiting the arrival of [[Jovica Stani<U+0161>i<U+0107>]] and [[Franko Simatovi<U+0107>]], who were acquitted at the [[ICTY|Hague Tribunal]].<ref>[http://www.telegraf.rs/vesti/728579-sacekao-ih-predrag-danilovic-stanisic-i-frenki-posle-10-godina-u-srbiji MO<U+0160>A: Novinari i Predrag Danilovi<U+0107> <U+010D>ekali Stani<U+0161>i<U+0107>a i Frenkija na aerodromu, do<U+010D>ekali <U+017D>eljka Mitrovi<U+0107>a!];telegraf.rs, 31 May 2013</ref><ref>[http://www.blic.rs/Vesti/Hronika/385636/Danilovic-uzalud-cekao-Stanisica-i-Simatovica Danilovi<U+0107> uzalud <U+010D>ekao Stani<U+0161>i<U+0107>a i Simatovi<U+0107>a];''Blic'', 1 June 2013</ref> After being on the run for more than two weeks, Filipovi<U+0107> got arrested in Belgrade on 2 June.<ref>[http://www.blic.rs/Vesti/Hronika/385821/Uhapsen-Branko-Filipovic-Fido-zbog-napada-na-Predraga-Danilovica Uhap<U+0161>en Branko Filipovi<U+0107> Fido zbog napada na Predraga Danilovi<U+0107>a];''Blic'', 2 June 2013</ref><ref>[http://www.mondo.rs/s292356/Info/Hronika_i_Drustvo/Uhapsen_napadac_na_Predraga_Danilovica.html Uhap<U+0161>en napada<U+010D> na Predraga Danilovi<U+0107>a];mondo.rs, 2 June 3013</ref> After initially being charged with "causing severe bodily harm with life-threatening injuries", his charge was in the meantime changed to "attempted murder" by the Serbian public prosecutor office.<ref>[http://www.blic.rs/Vesti/Hronika/385821/Tuzilac-promenio-krivicno-delo-Filipovicu-preti-i-do-40-godina-zatvora-za-napad-na-Danilovica Tu<U+017E>ilac promenio krivi<U+010D>no delo: Filipovi<U+0107>u preti i do 40 godina zatvora za napad na Danilovi<U+0107>a];''Blic'', 2 June 2013</ref>

